I see my influence there from a past question on here (this isn&#39;t an accusation, go ahead and use the code). 

I am not completely clear about what you are looking for, but I assume that you are seeking to somehow host a file at one link, but only allow access to that link through the temporary link. 

Here is what I came up with:

**models.py**
```
class OneTimeLink(models.Model):
    one_time_code = models.CharField(max_length=250)
    expiry_time = models.DateTimeField(default=datetime.now()+timedelta(hours=1), blank=True)
    video_code = models.CharField(max_length=250, default=&quot;XBRSJFLA&quot;)

    def __str__(self):
        return f&quot;{self.expiry_time}&quot;

class VideoLink(models.Model):
    url = models.CharField(max_length=250, default=&quot;THEVIDEOURL&quot;)
    pass_code = models.CharField(max_length=250, default=&quot;XBRSJFLA&quot;)

```

I created a separate video link model to handle ensuring that the person cannot return to the video URL later (i.e. it only works once). `url` is the link to the video and `pass_code` is meant to match with the `video_code`  in `OneTimeLink`.

**views.py**

```
def randomString(stringLength=20):
    &quot;&quot;&quot;Generate a random string of fixed length &quot;&quot;&quot;
    letters = string.ascii_lowercase
    return &#39;&#39;.join(random.choice(letters) for i in range(stringLength))

def generate_link(request):
    the_string = randomString(stringLength=20)
    OneTimeLink.objects.create(one_time_code=the_string)
    url = &#39;&lt;a href=&quot;/polls/one_time_link/{}&quot;&gt;{}{}&lt;/a&gt;&#39;.format(the_string, request.build_absolute_uri(), the_string)
    return HttpResponse(url)

```
The above code is what you have seen already. It generates a random string for the temporary link (as well as the temporary url for the video now) as well as the temporary link itself. 

```
def one_time_link(request, access_code=0):
    if OneTimeLink.objects.filter(one_time_code=access_code).exists():
        obj = OneTimeLink.objects.get(one_time_code=access_code)
        field_object = OneTimeLink._meta.get_field(&#39;expiry_time&#39;)
        expiry_time = field_object.value_from_object(obj)
        if expiry_time &lt; datetime.now(timezone.utc):
            #remove the line below if you do not want the link to self destruct after it has been used
            OneTimeLink.objects.filter(one_time_code=access_code).delete()
            video_var = VideoLink.objects.get(pass_code=obj.video_code)
            the_url = video_var.url
            return redirect(&#39;video_link&#39;,the_url)
        else:
            return HttpResponse(&quot;Bad or expired link.&quot;)
    elif not OneTimeLink.objects.filter(one_time_code=access_code).exists():
        return HttpResponse(&quot;Bad or expired link.&quot;)
    else:
        return HttpResponse(&quot;Bad or expired link.&quot;)
```

This code does the same as your existing `one_time_link`, except that instead of the `HttpResponse`, it obtains the `url` for the relevant video and redirects to that url. It goes to `video_link`, along with the url stored in the video link. 
```

def video_link(request, video_code):
    if VideoLink.objects.filter(url=video_code).exists():
        video_var = VideoLink.objects.get(url=video_code)
        video_var.url = randomString(stringLength=10)
        video_var.save()
        return HttpResponse(&quot;Here is your video. You can only access this with the link.&quot;)
    else:
        return HttpResponse(&quot;Nope. no video here. Go pay for it you thief!&quot;)
```
This is the video link url generator. It takes the `video_code` as the argument and checks for a `url` in `VideoLink` which matches. If it finds that the link is still valid, it changes the URL so it cannot be used again and serves the relevant content. 

**urls.py**
```
    path(&#39;one_time_link/&lt;str:access_code&gt;&#39;, views.one_time_link, name=&#39;one_time_link&#39;),
    path(&#39;video_link/&lt;str:video_code&gt;&#39;, views.video_link, name=&#39;video_link&#39;),
```

